headline.main: FRENCH BUY BREAD MADE OF U.S. FLOUR; Receipts From Those Able to Pay Go to Aid War Prisoners

abstract: Food and med aid: bread baked from U S flour gift distributed free, unoccupied France; those able to pay asked to give sum to Red Cross
